{
  "stem": "7177.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he was walking on the street in Germany, but he was completely bowled over forward, like he didn't want anybody to see anything.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then one thing I remember distinctly, I do not know remember the name.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My aunt Betty, the one I was named after her, her husband committed suicide in our house.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I mean, those were all things way before--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he had been a soldier in the First World War.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was a very proud bearer of a German, German cross, I do not-- [NON-ENGLISH] cross.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's it.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Iron Cross.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was a very proud-- and so when Hitler came, and they were-- you know, they-- they-- they lived in a big city.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they got almost immediately the reaction of the Hitler and whatever he did, he came to Holland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he just didn't want to live anymore, so he committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I never saw the actual fact, but I know that my father found him upstairs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so that's how I know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had a-- my mother had a maid.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was nothing special.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was not that we were rich, not at all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we had a maid.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my mother-- our maid would come each and every evening and would ask my mother, for how many people do you think I should cook today?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How many potatoes should I peel today?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because there were at least, at least, each and every day, we were so close to the German border, that everybody would come across the border, right there where we were.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And if anybody saw them and they would ask a question, my father was the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
